properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant snowfall expected beginning Tuesday. Total snowfall: 10 to 20 cm, with higher amounts possible inland and over higher terrain. Maximum wind gusts: up to 80 km/h. Locations: Channel-Port aux Basques and vicinity to Connaigre. Time span: midday Tuesday through Tuesday night. Remarks: Snow is expected to spread across southwestern Newfoundland on Tuesday. Strong winds will cause blowing snow and reduced visibility in some locations. In addition, the snow may change to rain over coastal areas on Tuesday night before the precipitation tapers off. Conditions will improve Wednesday morning. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Additional rainfall amounts of 30 to 40 mm tonight. A frontal system laden with subtropical moisture will move across B.C. South Coast tonight bringing rain to the region. Over Howe Sound and eastern sections of Lower Fraser Valley, steady rain will become heavy this evening. Squamish area has received over 42 mm rain since Saturday evening. Hope area is reporting 32 mm last 24 hours. Additional rainfall amounts of 30 to 40 mm are expected before the heavy rain tapers off overnight over Howe Sound and early Monday morning over eastern Fraser Valley. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.

properties.Summary:

Conditions will improve Wednesday morning. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada.
